question_data.full_text:
Project 2 entry
/project2
How to play:
Start by POSTing JSON to
/submit
with
{ email, secret, url, answer }
, using
url
=
/project2
.
After each submission, the response tells you if it is correct and, if allowed, the
next URL
. Open that URL in the browser to read the task-specific instructions.
Each task page clearly states the required answer format to unlock the next URL. Difficulty 1–2 always reveal the next link; difficulty 3–5 reveal it only when correct.
Some steps are personalized to your email (noted on the step page). Steps marked “Not personalized” accept the same answer for everyone.

question_data.full_text:
project2-gh-tree
/project2-gh-tree
Difficulty:
3 (next URL only on correct answer)
Personalized:
Yes. Add an offset based on your email length.
Use the GitHub API:
GET /repos/{owner}/{repo}/git/trees/{sha}?recursive=1
with params in
/project2/gh-tree.json
.
Count how many
.md
files are under
pathPrefix
.
Compute
offset = (length of your email) mod 2
. Final answer = count + offset.
Submit that integer as
answer
with
url
=
/project2-gh-tree
. Send the number only.
